{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"733975c7-df14-4ea6-a532-7c0123eaabb9","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n## 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\n`MSTest.Sdk` replaces the usual `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` and automatically pulls in MSTest runner, framework, and analyzers — no extra `<PackageReference>` items needed.\n\n## 2. Enable parallelism (`.runsettings` or assembly attribute)\n\nThe simplest way — add an assembly-level attribute in a file like `Usings.cs`:\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs all test **methods** in parallel. Use `ExecutionScope.ClassLevel` to parallelize across classes but run methods within a class sequentially.\n\n## 3. Sequential database tests\n\nMark your database test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Should_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Should_Read_After_Write() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nTests in this class will run sequentially **after** all parallelizable tests complete.\n\n### Summary\n\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---|---|\n| Minimal project | `MSTest.Sdk/3.7` as the SDK |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| Sequential opt-out | `[DoNotParallelize]` on class |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a3064f4c-be42-44a3-ac3f-a431cdf61546","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. The user is asking a general question about MSTest setup. Let me provide them with the recommended setup based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk.","outputTokens":476,"requestId":"6047:2A9B4:25959C0:2836261:6A03127D"},"id":"4c2c4782-09fb-4cfb-9e69-462cec3f329e","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:44:12.050Z","parentId":"792a0bf4-32a6-420c-9